Loved the concept and feel of this bar. Dimly lit, nice interior, great date spot. The staff was very helpful in choosing a wine flight from their extensive list. Also order the grilled bread if you really wanna have a neutral palette when tasting the wines and because the grilled bread is really good.

Amazing wine bar with some of the best wine selections in DC and an amazing and knowledgeable staff. Plus, their food is absolutely outstanding! I love to come here for dinner and highly recommend their fried chicken and a side of their potatoes! If you come to Flight, come for the drinks and stay for their food. I can’t wait to be back!

Hummus plate was delicious with the brussel sprouts as the star. $3 bread was not really worth it. Light on portion so I'd would have rather passed on it.

some of the best wine I've ever had - my husband took me here for a surprise - I was so happy! We got two flights and that was good enough! I don't remember leaving but I do remember the good times we had while we were there! cant wait to  come back!

Smart and engaged staff in a well put together space. List is a decent length, and the flight model works. A real something for everyone wine bar.

Great spot to stop by for those that love a nice glass of wine. The space is intimate with great lighting that matches the mood and atmosphere. We enjoyed seats at the bar, where you can enjoy a wine tasting and have conversation with the friendly bartender. Tastings are higher than your normal wine tastings but priced fairly for the amount of wine you get. We didn't get to try the food since we had just finished dinner around the corner but I look forward to coming back for more wine and a bite to eat. The menu is a little limited, so I may have to go back with the ladies instead of hubby. The Flight Wine Bar is definitely a perfect way to wine down.
Hmm. Excellent wine selection and great aparagus plate. I think for the quality and price,you can find better.

It felt like a place aimed at getting tourists in the door once and extracting as much money as possible. I really wanted to like this place as more wine bars are always a good thing, but it felt like they were trying harder to look like an expensive wine bar than actually getting good wines, having knowledgeable staff and great food pairings to be a really good wine bar.

With a well educated staff, and a varied wine list with an option for every palate, Flight is a winner for every wine lover. Our table ordered a rosé flight, a German white (Pinot Gris or Pinot Grigio; I forget because it was not my order), and a Spanish Tempranillo, and each of us were individually delighted with our choices (and could have happily tried at least three others).  The food was also excellent. We ordered one of each starter, and we especially loved the ricotta and the arancini.  Interesting notes: also available were a pleasant variety of spirits, and the menu featured indigenous wines.
Really great selection of wine. They have a full food menu and the service is great.
Great staff, knowledgeable service, great food, awesome atmosphere.  I'll be back!

Our son and his wife had their after wedding celebration at Flight.  It was amazing.  The food was superb.  The staff was attentive and professional.  The sommeliers were knowledgeable and very good at what they do. The staff bent over backswards to give us the best that they had to offer.  It was a very enjoyable and successful celebration.  Thenk you to everyone at Flight for making this event memorable for not only our son and his wife, but also for all the guests who attended.  Bernie and Jeff Karns

This is a really great place to have a few glasses of wine. If wine was their main focus I would have given them a 5. However. They also serve appetizers and dinner.  These seem to be tailored to the random casual diner rather than someone looking to experience a few different wines and expand their pallet. My first warning was that the place was dead. The bar tender laughed it off and suggested it was due to the holidays but I am not too sure. The place seems a bit stagnant and identity confused. Rap and hip-hop played while low lights and Italian influence catered the decor. The wine bar has an epic wood-worked display and stone tile serving semi-circle and yet they play music that appeals to a hip, younger crowd. I had an old world red flight and enjoyed 2/3 of the wines. I did not like #2 and the tender offered to and replaced it for free with something ‘fruitier’ as if I cannot palette a French wine due to the tones and not because I detest ‘cacao and licorice ‘ in a wine. I never drink without food so I ordered the potatoes. Their take on French fries include smashed fingerling potatoes doused in parm and salt. They sit in a little stack on top of ‘spicy garlic aioli ‘ which is spicy mayo mixed with garlic. The top potatoes can be dipped in the sauce, the bottom are overly saturated and lost to the thick, gelatinous sauce. Finally. Most egregious. No cheese and meat plates. You’re a wine bar! At least give me some olives!

I would definitely recommend this place to anyone looking to try to wines or trying to find a wine that they like. The staff is very knowledgeable and pleasant.

Excellent wine list, friendly and helpful staff, stylish yet laid-back atmosphere.  Their flights are terrific, and there are plenty of wine with which to build your own!  We love this place!
Got there on a Friday night at 9:30 and they chased us out after our first order cuz they wanted to close early!  What a joke.  No thanks.

This is a restaurant inside the Green Valley Casino that tends to be more upscale in service & price. I ordered steak & scallops & found both to be perfectly prepared. I like it. Came here after getting engaged. Nice wine list and great wine bar menu.

Our waitress was fantastic, very knowledgable and we pretty much had her pick the cheeses and pairs. We had French white, and Italian reds. Everything was perfect. Service was fantastic, wine was fantastic. My girlfriend and I enjoyed our time here very much and will be returning!

Went here for new years and did shots with our server; it was a hoot. Their selection is extensive and the staff in incredibly knowledgeable of their inventory and its nuances. The entrees, while delicious, are expensive and not very filling. I would recommend appetizers and desserts if you are in a group.
Outstanding service and impressive wine selection make this a must-visit for anyone into fermented grapes.

Warning: If you get a little queasy when you read items like "steak tartare (aka raw beef)" and "duck," I'd avoid this place. My wife was all about the menu, but I had a hard time finding anything appealing (except the stuffed acorn squash). In the end, we ordered a cheese plate and wine. The wine was great and they have a large list. The cheese was just average.  I wouldn't go back here. However, their happy hour seemed decent!

One of the best places in DC to get various wines from around the world. The staff is very friendly and will help you pick a wine to your liking. Food is also very good for light snacks and small bites.

Wonderful wine bar in the heart of DC! Flight offers a broad range of wines from all around the world. You can do a flight (taste and compare 3 wines side by side), or have wine by the glass or by the full/half bottle. They even offer beers, ciders, spirits, apéritifs, and digestifs for non-wine lovers.  I love the wine bar and the atmosphere. The gold-hued bar has a modern look to it, with a wooden wine shelf branching out into the ceiling. You can sit around the central half-circular bar or at one of the bar tables. Wines are poured into tumblers. The list of wines is quite extensive. Everything from reds to rosés, from the Loire Valley in France to Santorini, Greece.  All flights are $18. You can a flight of French whites, Greek whites, or Old World whites. There are light-bodied and full-bodied reds, Spanish reds, and even a category called "Hipster and Proud of It." I chose the Muscat Three Ways.  +Cooperatives of Samos, High Peaks, Muscat, Samos, Greece (2012) A: White rose, lychee // P: Pineapple, pear // F: Aromatic, dry finish // N: A cooperative representing all the growers in Samos. +Jorge Ordonez, Botani, Sparkling Moscatel, Malaga, Spain (2012) A: Jasmine, peach // P: Melon, honeysuckle // F: Sweet finish balanced by refreshing acid // N: Hand-harvested grapes. +Cooperatives of Samos, Muscat Vin Doux, Samos, Greece (Dessert) Apricot jam, butterscotch, and melon flavors with a sweet finish.  It was a wonderful flight of muscat wines. I especially liked the Jorge Ordonez. It was perfectly balanced. Not too sweet, with all the fantastic fruity tones in check. Very, very lovely. The Cooperatives of Samos dessert muscat wine was a tad too sweet for me. Next time, I'm just getting a glass of the Jorge Ordonez.  Lots of wines to try! They also serve food, from appetizers to small plates of fried cauliflower and grass-fed lamb to large plates of seafood bouillabaisse, hanger steak, and slow-cooked pork belly. Beautiful wine bar with extensive selection of wines to satisfy enough the toughest oenophile.  Happy hour from 5 to 7 p.m. weeknights and 10 p.m. to closing Saturdays and Sundays.

Perfect spot for after work drinks or date night!  Cozy, Beautiful, and oh so yummy!  I tried 3 flights and enjoyed them all (hey, it was date night!)!  Definitely get the cheese plate (with chocolate) and the wild mushrooms!

Great place!  I loved the ambience and the food was delicious. I really enjoyed the selection of wine flights, which allow you to sample three wines. I had the Spanish reds and my husband enjoyed the beer selection.  This is a nice place for a fun date night!

Very upbeat atmosphere with a friendly and attentive staff!!!  The owners go out of their way to ensure each and every customer is satisfied. The food and wine selections are very extensive and high in quality.   I was especially surprised and VERY please to find that Flight even has a premium draft beer selection for the non-wine drinker in your group.  I HIGHLY recommend Flight to all my friends who are going out in DC!!!

In a short trip to DC I was looking for a place for a dinner and a few drinks. After reading the reviews for Flight I wanted to go there and try the food. I was pleasantly surprised as the quality of food service and atmosphere was more than I expected. I had the pulled duck and it was excellent. I will definitely stop by the next time I´m in town.

A great place, friendly service, good atmosphere and the interior design is stunning. The selection of beer is interesting and there is a great selection of wine. It is a nice place to enjoy a drink with colleagues after work - or meet a friend for dinner The food is excellent, I enjoyed a pulled duck sandwich with the best fries ever. Given the quality of food and wine, the price is very good.

While the wine options are fabulous, I really enjoy the beers they offer as well. There are several items worth feasting on including the lamb, mushrooms, bouillabaisse, steak, and duck sliders with great fries.  They also keep the music at the right level so you don't get a headache or become unable to have a conversation.  The spot is great before or after a Caps or Wizards game.
A bit tiny, but good selection and friendly staff

This is what the neighborhood needs! Great and unique wine list. The servers and the owners have great suggestions for wines. It isn't the stuffy DC scene. Love the food, especially the new fetoosh salad with watermelon radish. The classics are still great like the branzino and duck sandwich.
Great neighborhood gem. Unique and interesting wine list with friendly service. Well paired food menu. Just a fun and easy place to hang out at. Definitely among the top three wine bars in DC.
Cool spot. Amazing selection of wine. Really helpful staff, interested in teaching about wine.
